---
description: Iceberg Agent Stack governance rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Do not read `.env`, private keys, credentials files, or secret values.
- Keep scaffold generation dry-run first.
- Require explicit human approval before writing generated files.
- Do not push, merge, or deploy production code autonomously.
- Mark generated scaffolds with AI metadata.
- Use the M5 plan files as source of truth because the mission brief is known to be wrong.
